          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio parchment manuscript of the Qurʾān; Qurʾānic text: Q 104:2-107:5. Script style: kūfī B.II. Currently only the image of the fol. 1 recto is given by the institution.  </p>
              <p>Cf. the website of the institution: <ref target="https://collections.lacma.org/node/240061.">https://collections.lacma.org/node/240061.</ref>  </p>
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="mysql_id_687875" n="1r">
              <title type="numeric" key="104:002:004-105:005:003">
                                    104:002:004-105:005:003
                                </title>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc>
                <support>
                  <p>Text division: Simple verse separators consist of groups of three small dashes arranged diagonally one above the other. Every fifth verse is marked by the <hi rend="italic">abǧad</hi>-letter <hi rend="italic">hāʾ </hi>in gold. The beginning of a new Sūrah is marked with the text in gold ink in the script style D, that contains the name of the new Sūrah <hi rend="italic">al-fīl</hi> and the number of verses. The heading is outlined with a tendril ornament also in gold with red and green/blue/ (?) dots. The beginning of the next Sūrah <hi rend="italic">quraiš </hi>is different from the previous one: instead of the name of the Sūrah, the first word of the first verse is written in gold followed by the number of verses: لاٮلڡ ارٮع اٮٮ. <hi rend="italic"> </hi> </p>
                </support>
                <extent>Folios: 
                                    <dimensions unit="mm"><width>166</width><height>258</height></dimensions>
                                </extent>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout writtenLines="0">0 - 0 lines to a page
                                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote/>
            </handDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <summary>
                                The main text is written in kūfī style B.II; Sūrah headings are written in the style D in gold ink. Diacritics are marked with small dots. Two layers of vocalisation can be traced in the manuscript: the first layer writes the vowel marks with red dots; the second layer uses the newer vocalisation system with the <hi rend="italic">fatḥah</hi>, <hi rend="italic">kasrah</hi>, <hi rend="italic">ḍammah</hi>, <hi rend="italic">sukūn </hi>etc. written in green ink.
                            </summary>
